h2. Problem
Change Bamboo to use the G1GC garbage collector and set min heap and max heap size to be equal (best practices for G1GC) by default to be in alignment with other Atlassian products.

h2. Suggested Solution
{code}
#
# The following 2 settings control the minimum and maximum given to the Bamboo Java virtual machine.  In larger Bamboo instances, the amounts will need to be increased.
# We recommend that the minimum and maximum be set to the same value.
#
: ${JVM_MINIMUM_MEMORY:=1024m}
: ${JVM_MAXIMUM_MEMORY:=1024m}

#
# The following are the required arguments need for Bamboo standalone.
#
: ${JVM_REQUIRED_ARGS:="-XX:+UseG1GC"}
{code}

h3. Problem Definition

Currently isn't possible to change the scheduled triggers of deployment environments through REST API.
h3. Suggested Solution

Add REST API method to change the scheduled triggers of deployment environments.
h3. Workaround

Use Java Specs to customize the Scheduled Deployment Trigger:
{code:java}
.triggers(new ScheduledDeploymentTrigger()
                            .cronExpression("Cron Expression"));
{code}

h3. Issue Summary
[Bamboo YAML Specs Reference|https://docs.atlassian.com/bamboo-specs-docs/6.3.0/specs-yaml.html#job-requirements]

{quote}
Implicit match type for requirements is Exists.
{quote}


This does not indicate that other BOOLEAN checks capable in Bamboo are not available in the YAML specs.

We only run an *exists* check on the requirement
{code:title=BambooYamlToSpecsConverterImpl.java line 144}
                yamlJob.getRequirements().stream()
                        .map(Requirement::exists)
                        .forEach(specsJob::requirements);
{code}

h3. Workaround

We need to update the documentation to make it clearer that _only_ *EXISTS* requirements can be defined in yaml Specs.
